<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	ITEM 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;BUSINESS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	A.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	DESCRIPTION OF BUSINESS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The business of National Presto Industries, Inc. (the &#x201C;Company" or &#x201C;National Presto&#x201D;) consists of three business segments.&nbsp;&nbsp;For a further discussion of the Company&#x2019;s business, the segments in which it operates, and financial information about the segments, please ref
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	er to Note L to t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	he Consolidated Financial Statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Housewares/Small Appliance segment designs, markets and distributes housewares and small electrical appliances, including pressure cookers and canners, kitchen electrics, and comfort appliances.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Defense segment manufactures 40mm ammunition, precision mechanical and electro-mechanical assemblies,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	medium caliber cartridge cases;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	performs Load, Assemble and Pack (LAP) operations on ordnance-related products primarily for the U.S. Gover
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	nment and prime contractors;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	produces and sells a variety of less lethal products and support accessories,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	provides training for the use of less lethal products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	and manufactures detonators, booster pellets, release cartridges, lead azide, and other military energetic devices and materials.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;The Absorbent Products segment manufactures and sells private label and branded adult incontinence products.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	1. Housewares/Small Appliance Segment
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Housewares and electrical appliances sold by the Company include pressure cookers and canners; the Presto Control Master&#xAE; heat control single thermostatic control line of skillets in several sizes, griddles, woks and multi-purpose cookers; deep fryers of various sizes; waffle makers; pizza ovens; slicer/shredders; electric heaters; corn poppers (hot air, oil, and microwave); dehydrators; rice cookers; microwave bacon cookers; coffeemakers and coffeemaker accessories; electric tea kettles; electric k
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	nife sharpeners;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	a line of kitchen gadgets;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	and timers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Pressure cookers and canners are available in various sizes and are fabricated of aluminum and, in the case of cookers, of stainless steel, as well.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	% of consolidated net sales were provided by cast products (griddles, waffle makers, die cast deep fryers, skillets and multi-cookers), and approximately 18% by noncast/thermal appliances (stamped cookers and canners, pizza ovens, corn poppers, coffee makers, microwave bacon cookers, dehydrators, rice cookers, tea kettles, electric stainless steel appliances, non-cast fryers and heaters).&nbsp;&nbsp;For the year ended December 31, 201

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	ended December 31,
</FONT>

	201
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Products are sold primarily in the United States and Canada directly to retailers and also through independent distributors.&nbsp;&nbsp;Although the Company has long established relationships with many of its customers, it does not have long-term supply contracts with them.&nbsp;&nbsp;The loss of, or material reduction in,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	sales to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	any of the Company's major customers could adversely affect the Company's business.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most housewares and electrical appliances are sourced from vendors in the Orient.&nbsp;&nbsp;(See
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Note J
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	to the Consolidated Financial Statements.)&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company has a sales force of 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	employees that sell to and service most customers.&nbsp;&nbsp;A few selected accounts are handled by manufacturers' representatives who may also sell other product lines.&nbsp;&nbsp;Sales promotional activities are conducted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	primarily
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	through the use of newspaper advertising.&nbsp;&nbsp;The business is seasonal, with the normal peak sales period occurring in the fourth quarter of the year prior to the holiday season.&nbsp;&nbsp;This segment operates in a highly competitive and extremely price sensitive environment.&nbsp;&nbsp;Increased costs that cannot be fully absorbed into the price of products or passed along in the form of price increases to the retail customer can have a significant adverse impact on operating results.&nbsp;&nbsp;Several
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage3"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	2
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	companies compete for sales of housewares and small electrical appliances, some of which are larger than the Company&#x2019;s segment and others which are smaller.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, some customers maintain their own private label, as well as purchase brokered product directly from the Orient.&nbsp;&nbsp;Product competition extends to special product features, product pricing,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	product quality,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	marketing programs, warranty provisions, service policies and other factors.&nbsp;&nbsp;New product introductions are an important part of the Company's sales to offset the morbidity rate of other products and/or the effect of lowered acceptance of seasonal products due to weather conditions.&nbsp;&nbsp;New products entail unusual risks.&nbsp;&nbsp;Engineering and tooling costs are increasingly expensive, as are finished goods that may not have a ready market or achieve widespread consumer acceptance.&nbsp;&nbsp;High-cost advertising commitments which may accompany such new products or may be required to maintain sales of existing products may not be fully absorbed by ultimate product sales.&nbsp;&nbsp;Initial production schedules, set in advance of introduction, carry the possibility of excess unsold inventories.&nbsp;&nbsp;New product introductions are further subject to delivery delays from supply sources, which can impact availability for the Company's most active selling periods.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Research and development costs related to new product development for the years 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	, and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	were absorbed in operations of these years and were not a material element in the aggregate costs incurred by the Company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Products are generally warranted to the original owner to be free from defects in material and workmanship for a period of one to twelve years from date of purchase, depending on the product.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company allows a sixty-day over-the-counter initial return privilege through cooperating dealers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Products are serviced through a corporate service repair operation.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company's service and warranty programs are competitive with those offered by other manufacturers in the industry.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company primarily warehouses and distributes its products from distribution centers located in Canton and Jackson, Mississippi.&nbsp;&nbsp;Selective use is made of leased tractors and trailers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company invests funds not currently required for business activities (see
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Note A(5)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	to the Consolidated Financial Statements).&nbsp;&nbsp;Income from invested funds is included in Other Income in the accompanying Consolidated Financial Statements.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Earnings from investments may vary significantly from year to year depending on interest yields on instruments meeting the Company's investment criteria, and the extent to which funds may be needed for internal growth, acquisitions, newly identified business activities, and reacquisition of Company stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 72PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	2.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Defense Segment&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	AMTEC Corporation was acquired on February 24, 2001, and manufactures 40mm ammunition, and precision mechanical and electro-mechanical products for the U.S. Department of Defense (DOD) and DOD prime contractors.&nbsp;&nbsp;AMTEC&#x2019;s 75,000 square foot manufacturing facility located in Janesville, Wisconsin is focused on producing niche market ordnance products (such as training ammunition, fuzes, firing devices, and initiators).&nbsp;&nbsp;AMTEC is also the prime contractor for the 40mm ammunition system to the DOD (more fully described below).&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Spectra Technologies LLC, a subsidiary of AMTEC, was acquired on July 31, 2003, and is engaged in the manufacture and delivery of munitions and ordnance-related products for the DOD and DOD prime con
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	tractors.&nbsp;&nbsp;Spectra maintains 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	,000 square feet of space located in East Camden, Arkansas, dedicated primarily to Load, Assemble and Pack (LAP) type work and during 2008, completed a facility which enabled it to perform LAP work for the 40mm systems program previously mentioned and referenced below.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Amron, a division of AMTEC, holds the assets that were purchased from Amron LLC on January 30, 2006.&nbsp;&nbsp;Amron manufactures cartridge cases used in medium caliber ammunition (20mm, 25mm, 30mm and 40mm) primarily for the DOD and DOD prime contractors, which includes the 40mm systems program previously mentioned and referenced below.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Amron manufacturing facility is 208,000 square feet and is located in Antigo, Wisconsin.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	AMTEC Less Lethal Systems, Inc., a subsidiary of AMTEC Corporation, holds the assets that were purchased from ALS Technologies, Inc, a small Arkansas manufacturer of less lethal ammunition, on November 1, 2011.&nbsp;&nbsp;The subsidiary&#x2019;s products include smoke and tear gas grenades, specialty impact munitions, diversionary devices and stun munitions, support accessories like launchers and gas masks, as well as training for the use of its products.&nbsp;&nbsp;The subsidiary&#x2019;s new state-of-the-art less lethal ammunition manufacturing and training facility, which was completed in 2013, is 54,000 square feet and is located in Perry, Florida.&nbsp;&nbsp;Previously, the subsidiary operated out of a 15,000 square foot facility in Bull Shoals, Arkansas.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Tech Ord, a division of AMTEC, holds the assets of Chemring Energetic Devices, Inc.&#x2019;s business located in Clear Lake, South Dakota and all of the real property owned by Technical Ordnance Realty, LLC that were acquired on January 24, 2014.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The 88,000 square f
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	oo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	t Clear Lake facility is a manufacturer of detonators, booster pellets, release cartridges, lead azide, and other military energetic devices and materials, and its major customers include US and foreign government agencies, AMTEC Corporation, and other defen
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	e contractors.&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The Defense segment competes for its business primarily on the basis of technical competence, product quality, manufacturing experience, and price.&nbsp;&nbsp;This segment operates in a highly competitive environment with many other organizations, some of which are larger and others that are smaller.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	On April 25, 2005, AMTEC Corporation was awarded the high volume, five-year prime contract for management and production of the Army&#x2019;s 40mm Ammunition System.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Army selected AMTEC as one of two prime contractors responsible for supplying all requirements for 40mm practice and tactical ammunition for a period of five years.&nbsp;&nbsp;AMTEC was awarded the majority share of requirements, and the Army estimated the total for the two contract awards, if all of the options were fully exercised, to be $1.3 billion.&nbsp;&nbsp;Deliveries under the contract exceeded $671,000,000, with final deliveries completed in 2013.&nbsp;&nbsp;On February 18, 2010, the Army awarded AMTEC a second five-year contract for the management and production of the 40mm Ammunition System.&nbsp;&nbsp;As in the original
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	five

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	During
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	June of 2015, the U.S. Army awarded AMTEC two contracts to develop the next generation of 40
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	mm
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	high and low velocity
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	training
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	rounds.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Two contracts, one in each category, were a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	lso awarded to other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	contractors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The value
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	s of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	AMTEC&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	high and low velocity development awards were $2,985,000 and $2,990,000, respectively.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The development performance periods for the two contracts extend through the first quarter of 2017.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each contract has three production option years beginning in 2018. If exercised, the first year would be at a low initial rate, while the last two years would be at a full productio
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	n rates.&nbsp;&nbsp;At the end of the development
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	period, the Army will select
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	the round
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	in each category that provide the best value, at which point it will decide whether to exercise the production options under the applicable contracts.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	During 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	, almost all of the work performed by this segment directly or indirectly for the DOD was performed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	on a fixed-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	price basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under fixed-price contracts, the price paid to the contractor is awarded based on competition at the outset of the contract and therefore is generally not subject to adjustments reflecting the actual costs incurred by the contractor, with the exception of some limited escalation clauses,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	which on the 2010 contract applied
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	to only three materials &#x2013; steel, aluminum and zinc.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Defense segment&#x2019;s contracts and subcontracts contain the customary provision permitting termination at any time for the convenience of the government, with payment for any work completed, associated profit and inventory/work in progress at the time of termination. The segment&#x2019;s business does not tend to be seasonal.
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	4
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	3. Absorbent Products Segment&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Absorbent Products segment business (Presto Absorbent Products, Inc.) was formed on November 21, 2001 to purchase assets from RMED International, a company that manufactured primarily private label diapers.&nbsp;&nbsp;On October 6, 2003, the segment purchased the assets of NCN Hygienic Products, Inc., a Marietta, Georgia company which manufactured adult incontinence products and puppy pads, which were likewise primarily private label products.&nbsp;&nbsp;Focus continues to be on private label, although branded product is produced under the &#x201C;PRESTO&#x201D; label.&nbsp;&nbsp;The absorbent products business is capital intensive.&nbsp;&nbsp;New absorbent product equipment is extremely complex.&nbsp;&nbsp;Not only is considerable time required to secure and install the equipment, but even more time is required to develop the requisite employee skill sets to utilize the equipment efficiently.&nbsp;&nbsp;Sales channels must be in place to sell the increased capacity that results from new equipment and improved efficiency in operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	In 2007
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	, the Company consolidate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	d
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	its adult incontinence production capabilities and relocat
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	ed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	its adult incontinence manufacturing equipment from its Marietta, Georgia facility to its Eau Claire, Wisconsin facility.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	At that time
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	it
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	discontinue
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	d
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	the manufacture of puppy pads.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Unlike the housewares/small appliance business, the absorbent product business is not seasonal.&nbsp;&nbsp;To the extent there are variations from month to month, that is primarily a function of customer promotional timing or a change in the customer base.&nbsp;&nbsp;As private label products tend to emulate branded product, new product development is important, but is largely limited to providing features similar to those found in national branded product.&nbsp;&nbsp;Research and development costs are absorbed in operations.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	The absorbent product industry is a very competitive, high volume-low margin business.&nbsp;&nbsp;There are several competitors, most of which are larger than this segment of the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;Product competition is largely based on product pricing, quality, and features.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Product cost is heavily influenced by commodity costs which include wood pulp, as well as many petroleum based products.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is also influenced by equipment operating speed, efficiency, and utilization.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Advertising is typically the responsibility of the owner of the private label and is thus minimal.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most sales are currently handled through distributor/brok
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	er arrangements.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	The segment, which realized its first significantly profitable year in 2009, began experiencing capacity constraints towards the end of that year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;To date, it has ordered four multi-million dollar machines,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	all
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	of which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	had been
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	installed in the Eau Claire, Wisconsin facility
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	by the end of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The segment also completed a warehouse addition to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	current facility in Eau Claire
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	and installed an automated handling system, both of which were in operation by the third quarter of 2011. Additional equipmen
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	t purchases are in process.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;As the segment is now outfitted with equipment to offer the full lineup of adult incontinent products required by private label retailers,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	a major national retailer will be placing the segment&#x2019;s briefs in all of its stores.&nbsp;&nbsp;Shipments are expected to begin in 2016.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 36PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	B.&nbsp;&nbsp;OTHER COMMENTS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 28.8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	1. Sources and Availability of Materials
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	See
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Note J
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	to the Consolidated Financial Statements.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	2. Patents, Trademarks, and Licenses
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Patents, particularly on new products, trademarks and know-how are considered significant to the Company&#x2019;s Housewares/Small Appliance segment.&nbsp; The Company's current and future success depends upon judicial protection of its intellectual property rights (patents, trademarks and trade dress).&nbsp; Removal of that protection would expose the Company to competitors who seek to take advantage of the Company's innovations and proprietary rights.&nbsp; The Company has dozens of U.S. and foreign patents pending and granted.&nbsp; Of those U.S. patents granted, the following is a non-exhaustive list of those relevant to current products and their expiration dates, assuming continued payment of maintenance fees (the date is the latest expiration date of the corresponding patents):&nbsp; Quick Release Appliance Cord Assemblies (US 6,719,576,
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	December 2022,&nbsp; and 6,527,570, October 2021), Rotatable Cooking Apparatus (US 6,125,740 and 6,354,194, March 2019),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Coffee brewer (US D695,064 December 2027), Griddle w/ folding legs (US 7,635,827 November 2027), Griddle w/ attached warming tray (US D674,656 January 2027), Low profile griddle (US D575,098 August 2022), Stirring popcorn maker (US D615,797 May, 2024)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	, and Parabolic Heater (US D633,189, February 2025).&nbsp; To date, the Company has vigorously protected its rights and enjoyed success in all its intellectual property suits.&nbsp; The Defense
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	3. Effects of Compliance with Environmental Regulations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	In May 1986, the Company's Eau Claire, Wisconsin, site was placed on the United States Environmental Protection Agency's (EPA) National Priorities List (NPL) under the Comprehensive Environmental Response, Compensation and Liability Act of 1980 (CERCLA) because of alleged hazardous waste deposited on the property.&nbsp;&nbsp;At year end 1998, all remediation projects at the Eau Claire, Wisconsin, site had been installed, were fully operational, and restoration activities had been completed.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Based on factors known as of December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	, it is believed that the Company's environmental liability reserve will be adequate to satisfy on-going remediation operations and monitoring activities; however, should environmental agencies require additional studies or remediation projects, it is possible the existing accrual could be inadequate.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Management believes that in the absence of any unforeseen future developments, known environmental matters will not have any material effect on the results of operations or financial condition of the Company.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	5. Industry Practices Related to Working Capital Requirements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	The major portion of the Company's sales was made with terms of 60 days or shorter.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	For the Housewares/Small Appliance segment, inventory levels increase in advance of the selling period for products that are seasonal, such as pressure canners, heaters, and major new product introductions.&nbsp;&nbsp;Inventory build-up also occurs to create stock levels required to support the higher sales that occur in the latter half of each year.&nbsp;&nbsp;Buying practices of the Company's customers require "just-in-time" delivery, necessitating that the Company carry large finished goods inventories.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	The multiple stock keeping units inherent in the private label absorbent product business, combined with the desire to avoid excessive machine changeover (which can have a negative impact on efficiency), necessitates the carrying of a large finished goods inventory in the Absorbent Product segment as well.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	The ability to meet U.S. Department of Defense demands also necessitates the carrying of large inventories in the Defense segment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	6.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Order
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Backlog
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Shipment of most of the Company's Housewares/Small Appliance products occurs within a relatively short time after receipt of the order and, therefore, there is usually no substantial order backlog.&nbsp;&nbsp;New product introductions may result in order backlogs that vary from product to product and as to timing of introduction.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 54PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<EFX_RISK_FACTORS>
<A NAME="FIS_RISK_FACTORS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	ITEM 1A. RISK FACTORS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company&#x2019;s three business segments described above are all subject to a number of risk factors, the occurrence of any one or more of which could have a significant adverse impact on the business, financial condition, or results of operations of the Company as a whole.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Housewares/Small Appliance Segment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Increases in the costs for raw materials, energy, transportation and other necessary supplies could adversely affect the results of the Company&#x2019;s operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company&#x2019;s suppliers purchase significant amounts of metals, plastics, and energy to manufacture the Company&#x2019;s products.&nbsp;&nbsp;Also, the cost of fuel has a major impact on transportation costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any increased costs that cannot be fully absorbed or passed along in the form of price increases to the retail customer can have a material adverse impact on the Company&#x2019;s operating results.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Reliance on third-party suppliers in Asia makes this segment vulnerable to supply interruptions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	and foreign business risks
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The majority of the housewares/small appliance products are manufactured by a handful of third-party suppliers in Asia, primarily in the People&#x2019;s Republic of China.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#x2019;s ability to continue to select and develop relationships with reliable vendors who provide timely deliveries of quality parts and products will impact its success in meeting customer demand.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most products are procured on a &#x201C;purchase order&#x201D; basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, the Company may be subject to unexpected changes in pricing or supply of products.&nbsp;&nbsp;There is no assurance that it could quickly or effectively replace any of its vendors if the need arose.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any significant failure to obtain products on a timely basis at an affordable cost or any significant delays or interruptions of supply may disrupt customer relationships and have a material adverse effect on the Company&#x2019;s business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage8"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	7
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	In addition, international manufacturing is subject to significant risks, including, among others, labor unrest, adverse social, political and economic conditions, interruptions in international shipments, tariffs and other trade barriers, legal and regulatory constraints and fluctuations in currency exchange rates. Although China currently enjoys &#x201C;most favored nation&#x201D; trading status with the United States, the U.S. Government has in the past proposed to revoke that status and to impose higher tariffs on products imported from China, which could have a material adverse effect on the Company&#x2019;s business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The Housewares/Small Appliance segment is dependent on key customers, and any significant decline in business from one or more of its key customers could adversely affect the segment&#x2019;s operating results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Although the Company has a long-established relationship with its major customers, it does not have any long-term supply agreement or guaranty of minimum purchases.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, the customers may fail to place anticipated orders, change planned quantities, delay purchases, or change product assortments for reasons beyond the Company&#x2019;s control, which could prove detrimental to the segment&#x2019;s operating results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The sales for this segment are highly seasonal and dependent upon the United States retail markets and consumer spending.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Traditionally, this segment has recognized a substantial portion of its sales during the Holiday selling season.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any downturn in the general economy
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	shift in consumer spending away from its housewares/small appliances
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	or deterioration in the financial health of its customer base
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	could adversely affect sales and operating results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The Company may not be successful in developing and introducing new and improved consumer products.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The development and introduction of new housewares/small appliance products is very important to the Company&#x2019;s long-term success.&nbsp;&nbsp;The ability to develop new products is affected by, among other things, whether the Company can develop and fund technological innovations and successfully anticipate consumer needs and preferences, as well as the intellectual property rights of others.&nbsp;&nbsp;The introduction of new products may require substantial expenditures for advertising and marketing to gain marketplace recognition or to license intellectual property. There is no guarantee that the Company will be aware of all relevant intellectual property in the industry and may be subject to claims of infringement, which could preclude it from producing and selling a product. Likewise, there is no guarantee that the Company will be successful in developing products necessary to compete effectively in the industry or that it will be successful in advertising, marketing and selling any new products.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Product recalls or lawsuits relating to defective products could have an adverse effect on the Company, as could the imposition of industry sustainability standards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	As distributors of consumer products in the United States, the Company is subject to the Consumer Products Safety Act, which empowers the U.S. Consumer Products Safety Commission to exclude from the market products that are found to be unsafe or hazardous.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under certain circumstances, the U.S. Consumer Products Safety Commission could require the Company to repair, replace or refund the purchase price of one or more of its products, or it may voluntarily do so. Any repurchase or recall of products could be costly and damage the Company&#x2019;s reputation, as well as subject it to a sizable penalty that the Commission is empowered to impose.&nbsp;&nbsp;If the Company removed products from the market, its reputation or brands could be tarnished and it might have large quantities of finished products that could not be sold.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The Company could also face exposure to product liability claims if one of its products were alleged to have caused property damage, bodily injury or other adverse effects. It is self-insured to specified levels of those claims and maintains product liability insurance for claims above the self-insured levels. The Company may not be able to maintain such insurance on acceptable terms, if at all, in the future.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, product liability claims may exceed the amount of insurance coverage.&nbsp;&nbsp;Moreover, many states do not allow insurance companies to provide coverage of punitive damages, in the event such damages are imposed.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, the Company does not maintain product recall insurance.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, product recalls or
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage9"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	8
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	product liability claims could have a material adverse effect on the Company&#x2019;s business, results of operations and financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The portable appliance and floor care companies&#x2019; industry association is in the process of trying to promulgate sustainability standards for the industry.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	It has p
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	assed an outline for a standard
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	but has not yet developed specific guidelines for implementation.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The Sustainability Consortium (TSC) under the auspices of a Retail Association (RILA) is trying to develop standards for all consumer products.&nbsp;&nbsp;If either the association or TSC is successful
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	in developing enforceable standards
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	, the standards are expected to ultimately become mandatory.&nbsp;&nbsp;The standards as drafted will do nothing for the environment, but will entail the addition of significant bureaucracy and outside certification fees.&nbsp;&nbsp;As such, compliance will be burdensome and expensive.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The housewares/small appliance industry continues to consolidate, which could ultimately impede the Company&#x2019;s ability to secure product placement at key customers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Over the past decade, the housewares/small appliance industry has undergone significant consolidation, and, as a result, the industry primarily consists of a limited number of larger companies.&nbsp;&nbsp;Larger companies do enjoy a competitive advantage in terms of the ability to offer a larger assortment of product to any one customer.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, the Company may find it more difficult or lose the ability to place its products with its customers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Defense Segment:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;BORDER-BOTTOM-STYLE:DOUBLE;BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH:2PT;HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company relies primarily on sales to U.S. Government entities, and the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	failure to procure or the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	loss of a significant contract or contracts could have a material adverse effect on its results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	As the Company&#x2019;s sales in the Defense segment are primarily to the U.S. Government and its prime contractors, it depends heavily on the contracts underlying these programs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The loss or significant reduction of a major program in which the Company participates could have a material adverse effect on the results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	A decline in or a redirection of the U.S. defense budget could result in a material decrease in the Defense segment sales and earnings.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Government contracts are primarily dependent upon the U.S. defense budget.&nbsp;&nbsp;During recent years, the Company&#x2019;s sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	augmented by increased defense spending, including supplemental appropriations for operations in Iraq and Afghanistan.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, future defense budgets could be negatively affected by several factors, including U.S. Government budget deficits, administration priorities, U.S. national security strategies, a change in spending priorities, and the reduction of military operations
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	around
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	the world.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any significant decline or redirection of U.S. military expenditures could result in a decrease to the Company&#x2019;s sales and earnings.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	U.S. Government contracts are also dependent on the continuing availability of Congressional appropriations. Congress usually appropriates funds for a given program on a fiscal year basis even though contract performance may take more than one year.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, at the outset of a major program, the contract is usually incrementally funded, and additional monies are normally committed to the contract by the procuring agency only as Congress makes appropriations for future fiscal years.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, most U.S. Government contracts are subject to modification if funding is changed.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any failure by Congress to appropriate additional funds to any program in which the Company participates, or any contract modification as a result of funding changes, could materially delay or terminate the program.&nbsp;&nbsp;This could have a material adverse effect on the results of the Company&#x2019;s operations.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
