<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage10"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	9
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The Company may not be able to react to increases in its costs due to the nature of its U.S. Government contracts.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Substantially all of the Company&#x2019;s U.S. Government contracts are being performed on fixed-price basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under fixed-price contracts, the Company agrees to perform the work for a fixed price, subject to limited escalation provisions on specified raw materials.&nbsp;&nbsp;Thus it bears the risk that any increases or unexpected costs may reduce profits or potentially cause losses on the contract, which could have a material adverse effect on results of operations and financial condition.&nbsp;&nbsp;That risk is potentially compounded by the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	political actions under consideration by federal and state governments, including climate change and labor regulations, which could have an impact if enacted or promulgated on the availability of affordable labor, energy and ultimately, materials, as the effects of the legislation/regulation ripple throughout the economy. In addition, products are accepted by test firing samples from a production lot.&nbsp;&nbsp;Lots typically constitute a sizable amount of product.&nbsp;&nbsp;Should a sample not fire as required by the specifications, the cost to rework or scrap the entire lot could be substantial.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s U.S. Government contracts are subject to termination.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	All of the Company&#x2019;s U.S. Government contracts can be terminated by the U.S. Government either for its convenience or if the Company defaults by failing to perform under the contract.&nbsp;&nbsp;Performance failure can occur from a myriad of factors, which include late shipments due to the inability to secure requisite raw materials or components or strikes or other labor unrest, equipment failures or quality issues which result in products that do not meet specifications, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;Termination for convenience provisions provide only for recovery of costs incurred and profit on the work completed prior to termination.&nbsp;&nbsp;Termination for default provisions provide for the contractor to be liable for excess costs incurred by the U.S. Government in procuring undelivered items from another source.&nbsp;&nbsp;If a termination provision is exercised, it could have a material adverse effect on the Company&#x2019;s business, results of operations and financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Failure of the Company&#x2019;s subcontractors to perform their contractual obligations could materially and adversely impact contract performance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Key components and services are provided by third party subcontractors, several of which the segment is required to work with by government edict.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under the contract, the segment is responsible for the performance of those subcontractors, many of which it does not control.&nbsp;&nbsp;There is a risk that the Company may have disputes with its subcontractors, including disputes regarding the quality and timeliness of work performed by subcontractors.&nbsp;&nbsp;A failure by one or more of the Company&#x2019;s subcontractors to satisfactorily provide on a timely basis the agreed-upon supplies or perform the agreed-upon services may materially and adversely impact the Company&#x2019;s ability to perform its obligations as the prime contractor.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Absorbent Products Segment:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;BORDER-BOTTOM-STYLE:DOUBLE;BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH:2PT;HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The Absorbent Products segment is dependent on key customers, and any significant decline in business from one or more of its key customers could adversely affect the segment&#x2019;s operating results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	One customer,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Medline Industries Holdings LP
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	, accounted for more than 10% of consolidated net sales in 2011.&nbsp;&nbsp;In fourth quarter 2011, Medline began operating its own absorbent products facility.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, sales to Medline for 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	and 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	declined significantly.&nbsp;&nbsp;During the last several years, the Absorbent Products segment has been implementing a customer diversification program to reduce its reliance on this customer and in the process has developed smaller, albeit new key customers whose loss could also adversely affect the segment&#x2019;s results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Increases in costs for raw materials, transportation, energy and other supplies could adversely affect the results of its operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	At times, the Company has experienced significant increases in its raw material, transportation, energy, and other supply costs primarily due to limited global supply and increased demand.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any increased costs that cannot be fully absorbed or passed along in the form of price increases to its customers could adversely affect
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage11"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	10
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	earnings.&nbsp;&nbsp;Global economic conditions, supplier capacity constraints and other factors could affect the availability of, or prices for, those raw materials.&nbsp;&nbsp;The risk is further compounded by the political actions under consideration by federal and state governments, including climate change and labor regulations, which could have an impact if enacted or promulgated on the availability of affordable labor, energy, and ultimately, materials, as the effects of the legislation ripple throughout the economy.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The Company may not be successful in developing and introducing new and improved absorbent products.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The development and introduction of new absorbent products is very important to long-term success.&nbsp;&nbsp;The ability to develop new products is affected by, among other things, whether the Company can develop and fund technological innovations and successfully anticipate consumer needs and preferences.&nbsp;&nbsp;The introduction of new products may require substantial expenditures for advertising and marketing to gain marketplace recognition or to license intellectual property. There is no guarantee that it will be aware of all relevant intellectual property in the industry and may be subject to claims of infringement, which could preclude it from producing and selling a product. Likewise, there is no guarantee that the Company will be successful in developing products necessary to compete effectively in the industry or that it will be successful in advertising, marketing and selling new products it develops.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The inability to operate the Company&#x2019;s manufacturing facility at or near full capacity could adversely affect the result of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The Absorbent Products segment is a very capital-intensive business, utilizing high cost, high-speed equipment.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since the segment operates in a market that is highly competitive with relatively low margins, it is essential to operate near full capacity to achieve high efficiencies and profitable financial results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Acquisition Risks:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	The Company may pursue acquisitions of new product lines or businesses.&nbsp;&nbsp;It may not be able to identify suitable acquisition candidates or, if suitable candidates are identified, it may not be able to complete the acquisition on commercially acceptable terms. Even if the Company is able to consummate an acquisition, the transaction would present many risks, including, among others: failing to achieve anticipated benefits or cost savings; difficulty incorporating and integrating the acquired technologies, services or products; coordinating, establishing or expanding sales, distribution and marketing functions, as necessary; diversion of management&#x2019;s attention from other business concerns; being exposed to unanticipated or contingent liabilities or incurring the impairment of goodwill; the loss of key employees, customers, or distribution partners; and difficulties implementing and maintaining sufficient controls, policies and procedures over the systems, products and processes of the acquired company. If the Company does not achieve the anticipated benefits of its acquisitions as rapidly or to the extent anticipated by management, or if others do not perceive the same benefits of the acquisition as the Company does, there could be a material, adverse effect on the Company&#x2019;s business, financial condition or results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#0000FF;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.5PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Information Technology System Failure or Security Breach Risks
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The Company relies on its information technology systems to effectively manage its business data, communications, supply chain, logistics, accounting, and other business processes. While the Company endeavors to build and sustain an appropriate technology environment, information technology systems are vulnerable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	damage or interruption from circumstances beyond the Company&#x2019;s control, including systems failures, viruses, security breaches or cyber incidents such as intentional cyber attacks aimed at theft of sensitive data, or inadvertent cyber-security compromises.&nbsp;&nbsp;A security breach of such systems could result in interruptions of the Company&#x2019;s operations, negatively impact relations with customers or employees, and expose the Company to liability and li
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	tigation, any one of which could have a negative impact on the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	results of operations or financial condition.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#x2019;s insurance coverage may not be adequate to cover all the costs related to cyber security attacks or disruptions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 50.4PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	2014 COMPARED TO 2013
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Readers are direct
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	ed to Note L, &#x201C;Busi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	ness Segments,&#x201D; to the Company&#x2019;s Consolidated Financial Statements for data on the financial results of the Company&#x2019;s three business segments for the years ended December 31, 2014 and 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	On a consolidated basis, sales decreased by $7,825,000 (2%), gross profit decreased by $2,151,000 (3%), selling and general expense increased by $1,985,000 (9%), and intangibles amortization increased by $11,324,000 (1,699%).&nbsp;&nbsp;Other income, principally interest, decreased by $365,000 (50%), while earnings before provision for income taxes decreased by $18,048,000 (31%), and net earnings decreased by $14,775,000 (36%).&nbsp;&nbsp;Details concerning these changes can be found in the comments by segment below.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Housewares/Small Appliance net sales decreased $11,572,000 from $137,225,000 to $125,653,000, or 8%, primarily attributable to a decrease in units shipped.&nbsp;&nbsp;Defense net sales increased by $15,347,000, from $206,198,000 to $221,545,000, or 7%, primarily reflecting shipments by its new division acquired during 2014 (&#x201C;Tech Ord&#x201D;), which is described
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	in Note P to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	the Company&#x2019;s Consolidated Financial Statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;Absorbent Products net sales decreased by $11,600,000 from $76,765,000 to $65,165,000, or 15%, and was primarily attributable to a decrease in units shipped, reflecting the ongoing shift in the segment&#x2019;s customer base.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Housewares/Small Appliance gross profit decreased $1,477,000 from $26,850,000 (20% of sales) in 2013 to $25,373,000 (20% of sales) in 2014, primarily reflecting the decrease in sales mentioned above.&nbsp;&nbsp;Defense gross profit increased $7,041,000 from $50,168,000 (24% of sales) to $57,209,000 (26% of sales), primarily reflecting the increase in sales mentioned above.&nbsp;&nbsp;Absorbent products gross profit decreased $7,715,000, from $2,334,000 to a loss of $5,381,000, largely reflecting the decrease in sales mentioned above, costs associated with the installation of new capital equipment and the absence of the prior year&#x2019;s insurance settlement of $683,000.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage17"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	16
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Selling and general expenses for the Housewares/Small Appliance segment were flat. Defense segment selling and general expenses increased $1,640,000, primarily reflecting increased costs of $1,030,000 associated with its recently acquired Tech Ord division mentioned above and increases in employee compensation and benefit costs of $827,000.&nbsp;&nbsp;Selling and general expenses for the Absorbent Products segment increased $287,000, primarily reflecting the absence of the prior year&#x2019;s gain on the sale of obsolete equipment.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Intangible assets primarily consist of the value of a government sales contract, product backlogs, and consulting and non-compete agreements recognized as a result of the acquisition of certain assets of DSE, Inc., more fully de
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	scribed in Note Q to the Company&#x2019;s Consolidated Financial Statements, and the value of customer relationships, trademark
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	s and non-compete agreements related to AMTEC Less Lethal Systems, Inc. (&#x201C;ALS&#x201D;), a reporting unit in the Company&#x2019;s Defense segment.&nbsp;&nbsp;ALS was formed in 2011 following the acquisition of certain assets of ALS Technologies, Inc.&nbsp;&nbsp;The intangible assets are all attributable to the Defense Products segment.&nbsp;&nbsp;The government sales contract intangible asset is amortized based on units fulfilled under the three year contract, while the other intangible assets are amortized on a straight-line basis that approximates economic use, over periods ranging from one to nine years.&nbsp;&nbsp;The increase in amortization is primarily attributable to the acquired government sales contract, under which significant shipments began in 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Intangible assets are evaluated for impairment whenever events or changes in circumstances indicate that the carrying amount of the assets may not be recoverable.&nbsp;&nbsp;During 2014, the Company noted that the carrying amount of the customer relationships, trademarks and non-compete agreements related to ALS mentioned above exceeded the undiscounted cash flows expected to result from their use.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, an impairment loss of $2,063,000 was recognized based on the Company&#x2019;s analysis comparing the fair value of the intangible assets and their carrying amounts.&nbsp;&nbsp;The fair value of the intangible assets was determined using a discounted cash flow model.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The Company recognizes the excess cost of acquired entities over the net amount assigned to the fair value of assets acquired and liabilities assumed as goodwill. Goodwill is tested for impairment on an annual basis at the start of the fourth quarter and between annual tests whenever an impairment is indicated, such as the occurrence of an event that would more likely than not reduce the fair value of the reporting unit below its carrying amount.&nbsp;&nbsp;Impairment losses are recognized whenever the implied fair value of goodwill is less than its carrying value.&nbsp;&nbsp;A goodwill impairment of $2,840,000 was recognized during 2013, related to ALS mentioned above.&nbsp;&nbsp;The impairment was recognized as a result of the Company&#x2019;s analysis comparing the implied fair value of the reporting unit&#x2019;s goodwill to its recorded carrying amount.&nbsp;&nbsp;The fair value used in the evaluation of the goodwill impairment was determined using a multiple of EBITDA approach and discounted cash flow estimates.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	During 2013, the Company adjusted its recorded liability for contingent consideration related to the 2011 acquisition of certain assets of ALS Technologies, Inc. mentioned above.&nbsp;&nbsp;During the fourth quarter of 2013, the Company estimated that the earnings targets for the three calendar years following the year of acquisition, upon which the contingent consideration liability was based, would be not be achieved.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, the entire contingent consideration liability of $3,000,000 was reversed.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The above items were responsible for the change in operating profit.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Other income decreased $365,000, which was primarily attributable to lower interest income resulting from decreased yields on lower dollars of marketable securities invested.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Earnings before provision for income taxes decreased $18,048,000 from $58,345,000 to $40,297,000.&nbsp;&nbsp;The provision for income taxes decreased from $17,093,000 to $13,820,000, which resulted in an effective income tax rate increase from 29% in 2013 to 34% in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;The increase in the tax rate is primarily attributable to a revision to the filing approach used for one of the states in which the Company files returns, resulting in a tax refund of $4,000,000, which was recorded in 2013.&nbsp;&nbsp;Net earnings decreased $14,775,000 from $41,252,000 to $26,477,000.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Based on the accounting profession&#x2019;s 2005 interpretation of cash equivalents under Financial Accounting Standards Board (&#x201C;FASB&#x201D;) Accounting Standard Codification (&#x201C;ASC&#x201D;) 230, the Company&#x2019;s variable rate demand notes have been classified as marketable securities. This interpretation, which is contrary to the interpretation that the Company&#x2019;s representative received directly from the FASB (which indicated it would not object to the Company&#x2019;s classification of variable rate demand notes as cash equivalents), has resulted in a presentation of the Company&#x2019;s Consolidated Balance Sheets that the Company believes understates the true liquidity of the Company&#x2019;s income portfolio.&nbsp;&nbsp;As of December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	and 201

	4

	, $1

	2

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	144
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	,000 and $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	3

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">

	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	of variable rate demand notes are classified as marketable securities.&nbsp;&nbsp;These notes have structural features that allow the Company to tender them at par plus interest within any 7-day period for cash to the notes&#x2019; trustees or remarketers and thus provide the liquidity of cash equivalents.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The Company expects to continue to evaluate acquisition opportunities that align with its business segments and will make further acquisitions, as well as continue to make capital investments in these segments per existing authorized projects and for additional projects if the appropriate return on investment is projected.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	See Items 1-A-2 and 1-A-3.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The Company has substantial liquidity in the form of cash and cash equivalents and marketable securities to meet all of its anticipated capital requirements, to make dividend payments, and to fund future growth through acquisitions and other means.&nbsp;&nbsp;The bulk of its marketable securities are invested in the tax-exempt
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	variable rate demand notes described above and in municipal bonds that are pre-refunded with escrowed U.S. Treasuries.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The Company intends to continue its investment strategy of safety and short-term liquidity throughout its investment holdings.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Cash provided by operating activities was $73,213,000 during 2014 as compared to $24,219,000 during 2013.&nbsp;&nbsp;The principal factors behind the increase in cash provided can be found in the changes in the components of working capital within the Consolidated Statements of Cash Flows.&nbsp;&nbsp;Of particular note during 2014 were net earnings of $26,477,000, which included total non-cash depreciation and amortization expenses of $21,819,000 and impairment of intangible assets charges of $2,063,000; decreases in accounts receivable and inventory levels; and decreases in deposits with vendors included in other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	assets and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	current assets.&nbsp;&nbsp;These were partially offset by decreases in net payables.&nbsp;&nbsp;Of particular note during 2013 were net earnings of $41,252,000, which included total non-cash depreciation and amortization expenses of
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
</HR>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	$8,944,000, and an increase in net payables.&nbsp;&nbsp;These were partially offset by increases in deposits with vendors included in other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	assets and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	current assets, inventory levels, and account receivable levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Net cash used in investing activities was $7,531,000 during 2014 as compared to $38,703,000 used during 2013.&nbsp;&nbsp;During 2014, the Company continued its expansion of the Absorbent Products segment by purchasing plant and equipment in the amount of $11,287,000.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company also acquired substantially all of the assets of Chemring Energetic Devices, Inc.&#x2019;s business located in Clear Lake, South Dakota, and all of the real property owned by Technical Ordnance Realty, LLC, which is describ
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	ed in Note P to the Co
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	mpany&#x2019;s Consolidated Financial Statements, totaling $10,534,000.&nbsp;&nbsp;These were partially offset by net maturities/sales of marketable securities of $13,983,000.&nbsp;&nbsp;Of note during 2013 were the acquisitions of machinery and equipment of $14,245,000 and a customer contract of $21,968,000, primarily related to the acquisition of a group of assets describe
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	d in Note Q to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Company&#x2019;s Consolidated Financial Statements; and the acquisition of plant and equipment of $22,011,000, related to the expansion of the Company&#x2019;s Absorbent Products and Defense segments. These were partially offset by net maturities/sales of marketable securities of $19,112,000.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Based on the accounting profession&#x2019;s 2005 interpretation of cash equivalents under Financial Accounting Standards Board (&#x201C;FASB&#x201D;) Accounting Standard Codification (&#x201C;ASC&#x201D;) 230, the Company&#x2019;s variable rate demand notes have been classified as marketable securities. This interpretation, which is contrary to the interpretation that the Company&#x2019;s representative received directly from the FASB (which indicated it would not object to the Company&#x2019;s classification of variable rate demand notes as cash equivalents), has resulted in a presentation of the Company&#x2019;s Consolidated Balance Sheets that the Company believes understates the true liquidity of the Company&#x2019;s income portfolio.&nbsp;&nbsp;As of December 31, 2014 and 2013, $13,600,000 and $15,579,000, respectively,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	of variable rate demand notes are classified as marketable securities.&nbsp;&nbsp;These notes have structural features that allow the Company to tender them at par plus interest within any 7-day period for cash to the notes&#x2019; trustees or remarketers and thus provide the liquidity of cash equivalents.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Cash flows from financing activities for 2014 and 2013 primarily differed as a result of an accelerated payment made in late December 2012 of the annual 2013 dividend. The acceleration was occasioned by the uncertainty over the federal income tax rates that would be in effect in 2013. In contrast, the annual 2014 dividend payment was made during the first quarter of 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	As a result of the foregoing factors, cash and cash equivalents increased in 2014 by $31,090,000 to $54,043,000.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:45.35PT;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:444.25PT;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	(1)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Purchase obligations includes outstanding purchase orders at December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Included are purchase orders issued to the Company&#x2019;s housewares manufacturers in the Orient, to equipment manufacturers of absorbent products machinery, and to material suppliers and building contractors in the Defense and Absorbent Products segments.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company can cancel or change many of these purchase orders, but may incur costs if its supplier cannot use the material to manufacture the Company&#x2019;s or other customers&#x2019; products in other applications or return the material to their supplier.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, the actual amount the Company is obligated to pay cannot be estimated.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 10.8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT: -10.8PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Critical accounting policies
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The preparation of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Consolidated Financial Statements in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States requires management to make certain estimates and assumptions that affect the amount of reported assets and liabilities and disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities at the date of the Consolidated Financial Statements and revenues and expenses during the periods reported.&nbsp;&nbsp;Actual results may differ from those estimates.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company reviewed the development and selection of the critical accounting policies and believes the following are the most critical accounting policies that could have an effect on the Company&#x2019;s reported results.&nbsp;&nbsp;These critical accounting policies and estimates have been reviewed with the Audit Committee of the Board of Directors.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Inventories
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	New Housewares/Small Appliance product introductions are an important part of the Company&#x2019;s sales to offset the morbidity rate of other Housewares/Small Appliance products and/or the effect of lowered acceptance of seasonal products due to weather conditions.&nbsp;&nbsp;New products entail unusual risks and have occasionally
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	in the past
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	resulted in losses related to obsolete or excess inventory as a result of low or diminishing demand for a product.&nbsp;&nbsp;There were no such obsolescence issues that had a material effect during the current year and, accordingly, the Company did not record a reserve for obsolete product.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the future should product demand issues arise, the Company may incur losses related to the obsolescence of the related inventory.&nbsp;&nbsp;Inventory risk for the Company&#x2019;s other segments is not deemed to be significant, as products are largely built pursuant to customers&#x2019; specific orders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Self Insured Product Liability &amp; Health Insurance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The Company is subject to product liability claims in the normal course of business and is self-insured for health care costs, although it does carry stop loss and other insurance to cover claims once a health care claim reaches a specified threshold.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#x2019;s insurance coverage varies from policy year to policy year, and there are typically limits on all types of insurance coverage, which also vary from policy year to policy year. Accordingly, the Company records an accrual for known claims and incurred but not reported claims, including an estimate for related legal fees in the Company&#x2019;s Consolidated Financial Statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company utilizes historical trends and other analysis to assist in determining the appropriate accrual.&nbsp;&nbsp;There are no known claims that would have a material adverse impact on the Company beyond the reserve levels that have been accrued and recorded on the Company&#x2019;s books and records.&nbsp;&nbsp;An increase in the number or magnitude of claims could have a material impact on the Company&#x2019;s financial condition and results of operations.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Sales and Returns
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Sales are recorded net of discounts and returns.&nbsp;&nbsp;The latter pertain primarily to warranty returns, returns of seasonal items, and returns of those newly introduced products sold with a return privilege. The calculation of warranty returns is based in large part on historical data, while seasonal and new product returns are primarily developed using customer provided information.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Impairment and Valuation of Long-lived Assets
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The Company reviews long-lived assets for impairment whenever events or changes in circumstances indicate that the related carrying amounts may not be recoverable. Long-lived assets consist of property, plant and equipment and intangible assets, including the value of a government sales contract, customer relationships, trademarks, product backlogs, and consulting and non-compete agreements. Determining whether an impairment has occurred typically requires various estimates and assumptions, including determining which cash flows are directly related to the potentially impaired asset, the useful life over which cash flows will occur, the amounts of the cash flows and the asset&#x2019;s residual value, if any. In turn, measurement of an impairment loss requires a determination of fair value, which is based on the best information available. The Company uses internal discounted cash flows estimates, quoted market prices when
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

<EFX_MARKET_RISK>
<A NAME="FIS_MARKET_RISK"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	ITEM 7A.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	QUANTITATIVE AND QUALITATIVE DISCLOSURES ABOUT MARKET RISK
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The Company's interest income on cash equivalents and marketable securities is affected by changes in interest rates in the United States.&nbsp;&nbsp;Cash equivalents primarily consist of money market funds. Based on the accounting profession&#x2019;s interpretation of cash equivalents under FASB ASC 230, the Company&#x2019;s 7-day variable rate demand notes are classified as marketable securities rather than as cash equivalents.&nbsp;&nbsp;The demand notes are highly liquid instruments with interest rates set every 7 days that can be tendered to the trustee or remarketer upon 7 days notice for payment of principal and accrued interest amounts.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 7-day tender feature of these variable rate demand notes is further supported by an irrevocable letter of credit from highly rated U.S. banks.&nbsp;&nbsp;To the extent a bond is not remarketed at par plus accrued interest, the difference is drawn from the bank&#x2019;s letter of credit.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company has had no issues tendering these notes to the trustees or remarketers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Other than a failure of a major U.S. bank, there are no known risks of which the Company is aware that relate to these notes in the current market.&nbsp;&nbsp;The balance of the Company&#x2019;s investments is held primarily in fixed rate municipal bonds with an average li
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	fe of 1.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	year.&nbsp;&nbsp;Acco
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	rdingly, changes in interest rates have not had a material effect on the Company, and the Company does not anticipate that future exposure to interest rate market risk will be material.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company uses sensitivity analysis to determine its exposure to changes in interest rates.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The Company has no history of, and does not anticipate in the future, investing in derivative financial instruments.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most transactions with international customers are entered into in U.S. dollars, precluding the need for foreign currency cash flow hedges.&nbsp;&nbsp;As the majority of the Housewares/Small Appliance segment&#x2019;s suppliers are located in China, periodic changes in the U.S. dollar and Chinese Renminbi (RMB) exchange rates do have an impact on that segment&#x2019;s product costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is anticipated that any potential material impact from fluctuations in the exchange rate will be to the cost of products secured via purchase orders issued subsequent to the revaluation.
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_MARKET_RISK>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	CONTROLS AND PROCEDURES
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 12PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The Company's management, including the Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer, have conducted an evaluation of the effectiveness of the design and operation of the Company's disclosure controls and procedures pursuant to Rule 13a-15 under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (the &#x201C;1934 Act&#x201D;) as of December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on that evaluation, the Company&#x2019;s Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer concluded that the Company&#x2019;s disclosure controls and procedures were effective as of that date.
</FONT>
</P>

</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	There were no changes to internal control over financial reporting during the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	quarter ended December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	that have materially affected, or are reasonably likely to materially affect, the Company&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	MANAGEMENT&#x2019;S ASSESSMENT OF INTERNAL CONTROL OVER FINANCIAL REPORTING
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The management of National Presto Industries, Inc. is responsible for establishing and maintaining adequate internal control over financial reporting as defined in Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f) under the 1934 Act.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#x2019;s internal control system was designed to provide reasonable assurance to the Company&#x2019;s management and Board of Directors regarding the preparation and fair presentation of published financial statements.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	All internal control systems, no matter how well designed, have inherent limitations.&nbsp;&nbsp;Therefore, even those systems determined to be effective can provide only reasonable assurance with respect to financial statement preparation and presentation.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Management assessed the effectiveness of the Company&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting as of December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;In making this assessment, it used the criteria set forth by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission (COSO) in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Internal Control &#x2013; Integrated Framewo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	rk (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	2013
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	. Based on our assessment and those criteria, management concluded that, as of December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	, the Company&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting, as defined in Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f) of the 1934 Act, was effective.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	The Company&#x2019;s independent registered public accounting firm has issued its report on the effectiveness of the Company&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting.&nbsp;&nbsp;The report appears below.
</FONT>
</P>

<EFX_AUDITORS_OPINION>
<A NAME="FIS_AUDITORS_OPINION"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	REPORT OF INDEPENDENT REGISTERED PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Board of Directors and Stockholders
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	National Presto Industries, Inc.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Eau Claire, Wisconsin
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	We have audited National Presto Industries, Inc.&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting as of December 31, 2015, based on criteria established in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Internal Control &#x2013; Integrated Framework
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	(2013)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission (the COSO criteria).&nbsp;&nbsp;National Presto Industries, Inc&#x2019;s management is responsible for maintaining effective internal control over financial reporting and for its assessment of the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting, included in the accompanying Item 9A, Management&#x2019;s Assessment of Internal Control over Financial Reporting.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our responsibility is to express an opinion on the company&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting based on our audit.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	We conducted our audit in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States).&nbsp;&nbsp;Those standards require that we plan and perform the audit to obtain reasonable assurance about whether effective internal control over financial reporting was maintained in all material respects.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our audit included obtaining an understanding of internal control over financial reporting, assessing the risk that a material weakness exists, and testing and evaluating the design and operating effectiveness of internal control based on the assessed risk.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our audit also included performing such other procedures as we considered necessary in the circumstances.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that our audit provides a reasonable basis for our opinion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	A company&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting is a process designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	reliability
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles.&nbsp;&nbsp;A company&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting includes those policies and procedures that (1) pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable detail, accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the assets of the company; (2) provide reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles, and that receipts and expenditures of the company are being made only in accordance with authorizations of management and directors of the company; and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition, use, or disposition of the company&#x2019;s assets that could have a material effect on the financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage23"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	22
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	Because of its inherent limitations, internal control over financial reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements.&nbsp;&nbsp;Also,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	projections
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	of any evaluation of effectiveness to future periods are subject to the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions, or that the degree of compliance with the policies or procedures may deteriorate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	In our opinion, National Presto Industries, Inc. maintained, in all material respects, effective internal control over financial
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	reporting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	as of December 31, 2015, based on the COSO criteria.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	We also have audited, in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States), the consolidated balance sheets of National Presto Industries, Inc. as of December 31, 2015 and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	, and the related consolidated statements of comprehensive income, stockholders&#x2019; equity, and cash flows for each of the three years in the period ended December 31, 2015 and our report dated March 15, 2016 expressed an unqualified opinion thereon.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	/s/ BDO USA, LLP
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Milwaukee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	, Wisconsin
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:COURIER NEW;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
